<TEXT>
masked men set off explosives that 
destroyed 80 apartments under construction in a tourist complex 
police said the separatist corsican national liberation front 
claimed responsibility 
police said two men wearing hoods tied up 11 people living at 
the site mostly construction workers and drove them to a village 
15 miles away before detonating the blast early monday in the 
apartment complex in calvi on the northwestern coast of this french 
mediterranean island 
no injuries were reported 
the corsican national liberation front claimed responsibility in 
a statement made public in the bastia the nearest major city 
saying it was fighting speculative enterprises which will lead 
eventually to the marginalization of our people on their own land 
a similar attack last month destroyed 135 apartments under 
construction at santa lucia di porto vecchio in southeastern 
corsica 
