workers and to create productive civilian jobs for them 
what are they going to work at he demands making shoes 
eightfive percent of our shoes are imported consumer electronics 
all imported machine tools half are imported 
moreover melman argues defense managers are incapable of 
making the leap without retraining 
no major militaryserving enterprise has demonstrated an 
autonomous ability to carry out the sort of occupational switch 
that is needed to go civilian melman wrote in his book 
profits without production 
if you unleash these people the us will turn into a 
thirdrate economy melman says they cant hack it we will 
lose the capability of repairing the damage 
under a conversion legislation sponsored by rep ted weiss 
dny defense contractors would be required to put 125 percent 
of receipts into a fund to pay the costs of economic adjustment 
laidoff workers might get 90 percent of their lost salaries while 
they are retrained for civilian jobs 
gordon adams director of the defense budget project a 
washingon research outfit says workers find work when the 
economy is healthy you can plan the dickens out of what to do with 
a worker but when were in a recession you cant do anything for 
him 
adams says although counseling retraining and relocation 
programs are critical income supplements however slow the 
adjustment process 
