report 
the washington post reported that bush ordered the pentagon 
study of us defense strategy shortly after his election for help 
in dealing with soviet president mikhail s gorbachev 
a 26page executive summary of the secret report states there 
is broad agreement within the us intelligence community that 
the soviet union under gorbachev has decided to reverse a 20year 
pattern of growth in soviet military spending and force structure 
in order to boost the civil economy and soviet foreign policy 
the post said 
until a month ago bush and senior advisers criticized what they 
said was an increase in soviet defense spending as they pressed 
congress to approve the nearly 300 billion defense budget for 
fiscal 1990 
a white house spokesman interviewed by the post about the 
classified report said when it was written people were trying 
to prognosticate on the basis of soviet announcements and very 
early indications of soviet behavior in fact at that time our 
estimates were that there were few if any changes 
