<TEXT>
vp singh the man who reluctantly 
agreed to become prime minister of india has set out to prove hes 
in control 
as head of indias first minority government singh doesnt have 
a blank check to launch the revolutionary economic and social 
reforms that could allow india to join the ranks of the great 
powers in the next century 
but political observers and associates say the 58yearold prime 
minister has two things working in his favor a clean slate and a 
clean name 
within a week of taking the oath of office singh had reassured 
two embittered religious minorities they indeed have an important 
place in officially secular predominantly hindu india 
he appointed influential colleagues to lowerranking cabinet 
posts thereby denying them new power bases the more powerful 
posts went to men with the experience to push through change and 
the reputations for incorruptibility 
singhs fiveparty national front coalition denied prime 
minister rajiv gandhis congress party a majority in the nov 2226 
elections and brought down the nehru family dynasty that dominated 
indian politics since the country became independent from britain 
42 years ago 
but singh needs the continuing allegiance of both the hindu 
fundamentalists and the communists for his middleoftheroad 
alliance to muster a majority in parliament 
given the fragilility of this alliance many political observers 
are skeptical of the new governments ability to enact any major 
changes in the worlds largest democracy a country of 880 million 
people skewed between abject poverty and spaceage achievements 
the problems singh inherited are enormous but the 
mildmannered introverted politician who reluctantly agreed to 
head indias newest government has not been shy about what he 
intends to accomplish 
he lists his missions thus to eliminate poverty halt rising 
food prices that have doubled in the past year decentralize 
federal power reduce bureaucratic regulations and political 
meddling open the economy to western investors eager to do 
business with india and patch up differences with neighboring 
pakistan nepal and sri lanka 
foreign policy is a low priority for change 
singh has said he will not deviate from the course india has 
already charted between the worlds superpowers india he said 
will remain nonaligned and continue to build on its friendly 
relations with moscow and washington 
the first major test of singhs government provided it 
survives a confidence vote in parliament later this month will 
come during legislative elections in nine states in march and 
april all but two of the states now are dominated by gandhis 
congress party 
if congress loses it will split and the national front 
alliance will become stronger if congress defends its territory 
it will give renewed confidence to gandhi and his party and weaken 
our coalition then any constructive cooperation between us and the 
opposition will end said one national front member speaking on 
condition of anonymity 
but analysts say singhs most immediate problems stem from 
factional disputes within his own janata dal or peoples party 
the largest group in the fiveparty national front those 
differences surfaced again recently during wrangling for cabinet 
posts 
singh appointed a moslem as head of the powerful home ministry 
a move seen as an attempt to span the growing rifts between the 
majority hindus and the minority moslems that erupted into riots in 
which at 300 people were killed this fall 
later he visited the northern state of punjab the hotbed of 
the sikh separatist movement and offered prayers at the sikhs 
holiest shrine the golden temple the visit by singh a hindu was 
the first by an indian prime minister in more than five years and 
an effort to end the bloody secessionist campaign that has claimed 
more than 12000 lives since 1982 
a nation is not a map on a piece of paper singh later said 
it lives in the hearts of the people and if the hearts are 
divided the nation stands divided we will not allow this to 
happen 
despite speculation that singh would keep the finance portfolio 
which he held for two years under gandhi he gave it to a veteran 
lawmaker who is expected to continue if not speed up the reforms 
singh sees as needed to make india a competitor in the world 
markets 
instead singh kept the defense portfolio a signal that he will 
wield considerable power since defense spending has received the 
biggest chunk of the national budget 
the move prompted speculation singh would be directly involved 
in investigation into controversial arms deals during the gandhi 
administration 
government corruption was the linchpin in the national fronts 
campaign against gandhi and the congress party and earned singh the 
nickname the new mr clean a reference to similar promises 
that gandhi made to clean up indias bureacracy 
gandhi was buffeted by accusations that highly placed indians 
received up to 50 million in kickbacks from the swedish arms firm 
ab bofors winner of a 1986 contract to sell 14 billion worth of 
howitzers to the indian government 
gandhis denials that any indians profited from the bofors deal 
paled before detailed newspaper investigations but the accusations 
have not been proved 
singh said there will be an investigation but not a vendetta 
i want to make it clear that we will not be vindictive 
singh said no scandal will be cooked up against him or anyone 
else the law of the land will prevail 
