<TEXT>
a disbarred lawyer just out of 
jail becomes deputy premier with partial responsibility for police 
a dissident journalist who also has done time and most recently 
stoked coal in a factory is named foreign minister 
a bank clerk takes over the finance ministry 
the appointments sunday show just how utterly a 3weekold 
peaceful popular revolt has turned czechoslovak politics on end 
the swift smooth revolution has ousted the leaders of the 
crackdown that followed the suppression of the 1968 prague spring 
reforms out are those who stripped of party membership half a 
million communists deemed too reformist 
many of the persecuted also lost all access to anything but the 
most menial jobs now those who suffered are returning with 
remarkable ease to take center stage in national politics 
the revolt has brought the ebullient jiri dienstbier working as 
a stoker since he last got out of jail in 1982 back to his 
original profession journalism a job he lost in the crackdown on 
prague spring reforms 
the only difference is that instead of writing stories 
dienstbier gave them out as spokesman for the civic forum 
opposition coalition 
now he is to serve as foreign minister a role civic forum 
thinks he is suited for because of his fluent english and french 
and experience in the far east and the united states in the 
mid1960s as a correspondent for state radio 
after he lost that job and his communist party membership 
