<TEXT>
here at a glance are highlights of actions 
taken monday by the supreme court 
 
age discrimination 
 
the court ruled that federal judges may help plaintiffs in age 
discrimination suits try to find other possible victims and seek 
their participation in such suits 
the justices by a 72 vote ruled against hoffmannla roche 
inc which is accused of bias against older workers in laying off 
some 1200 employees at new jersey plants 
the high court said judges in such class action suits may 
help plaintiffs locate other possible victims of discrimination 
who may be unaware of the lawsuit and solicit their participation 
the case is hoffmannla roche vs sperling 881203 
 
nofziger 
 
the court refused to reinstate former white house aide lyn 
nofzigers conviction on charges of illegal lobbying after he left 
the reagan administration 
the justices without comment let stand a federal appeals court 
ruling that overturned nofzigers 1988 conviction 90day jail 
sentence and 30000 fine 
the case is us vs nofziger 89719 
 
freedom of information 
 
the court shielded the fbi from having to give grumman corp 
documents received from another government agency narrowing the 
reach of the freedom of information act 
by a 63 vote the court said the documents can be withheld 
because they were compiled for law enforcement purposes and 
therefore are exempt from the 1966 law aimed at curtailing 
government secrecy 
the case is john doe agency vs john doe corp 881083 
 
seatbelts 
 
the court turned away an appeal by an iowa woman battling her 
states mandatory seatbelt law 
the justices without comment refused to hear linda diane 
clarks arguments that the law similar to those in most states 
violates her constitutional rights 
the case is clark vs iowa 89687 
 
multinational corporations 
 
the court limited the way multinational corporations can use 
foreign tax laws to reduce their us taxes a ruling the bush 
administration said may save the government hundreds of millions of 
dollars 
the court ruled unanimously against goodyear tire and rubber co 
in a case stemming from operations of goodyears british subsidiary 
in the early 1970s 
the case is us vs goodyear 881474 
