kitchell and giles may be getting more than just a kick out of 
life 
we think differently as we get older in a slower manner and 
there is some memory loss which is a perfectly normal finding 
said dr robert bender of the mercy hospital geriatric clinic 
but there is some evidence that staying mentally active may 
actually help preserve brain function 
mental lethargy and its effects on good health can be seen most 
easily in nursing home patients said dr roy overton another 
gerontologist at mercy 
in nursing home patients we see these pseudo dementias that 
arent real dementias at all you walk into a room and see a 
patient staring at the ceiling or the floor and you think theyve 
lost their minds but they havent theyre truly depressed said 
overton 
bender tells his patients to write down their talents and use 
