<TEXT>
if jaguars and diamonds are a little pricey and 
storebought baubles arent personal enough for those on your list 
gifts fresh from your kitchen in attractive reusable containers 
make doubly delightful presents 
the time thoughtfulness and care that go into something 
handmade touch us all and part of the pleasure is looking for 
reusable containers ive found them in all sorts of places 
importexport stores have pottery glass baskets from all over 
the world a thrift or antique shop may unearth a charming tray or 
vintage mason jars and local artisans offer oneofakind pieces 
for the kitchen and home that will be treasured for years 
anything will be happily received from a cut glass cruet for 
your homemade vinegar to a tiny tiered jewelry box with each 
drawer filled with tantalizing twobite confections 
