monday 
the merger with first federal savings and loan association of 
pittsburgh is subject to government approval also needed is 
satisfactory completion of a review of first federal by pittsburgh 
national and approval of the board of directors of pittsburgh 
nationals parent company pnc financial corp the nations 
13thlargest bank holding company 
the merger will not require a cash payment by pittsburgh 
national or the issuance of additional shares by pnc financial 
since first federal is a mutual institution 
once the transaction is completed pittsburgh national said it 
will have about 20 billion in assets 
some bank branches will be closed but employees of those 
offices will be offered other jobs said pittsburgh national 
president james e rohr 
first federal has 3 billion in assets primarily comprised of 
mortgagerelated products it is the 88th largest thrift 
nationwide first federal has more than 700 fulltime and 200 
parttime employees and operates 64 branches in western 
pennsylvania 
pittsburgh national has more than 4200 employees it operates 
113 branch offices in pennsylvania 
pittsburghbased pnc was formed in 1983 by the consolidation of 
pittsburgh national corp and provident national corp of 
philadelphia as of sept 30 pnc reported 431 billion in assets 
and more than 17000 employees 
pnc operates 529 community banking offices in pennsylvania 
kentucky indiana ohio delaware and new jersey 
