<TEXT>
u s west and three international 
partners have been awarded an operating license to provide a new 
type of portable telephone system called personal communications 
networks in the united kingdom officials said 
pcns are heralded as the next generation of mobile 
communications technology they differ from the cellular phone 
systems of today in that they will operate on a different frequency 
and use more and smaller cell sites allowing a much greater volume 
of calls to be supported a cell site is an area served by a 
transmission tower that relays calls 
the project will cost an estimated 14 billion to develop and 
implement over a 12year period starting in 1992 or 1993 said ed 
mattix a spokesman for u s west international 
other companies in the unitel consortium are stc a british 
electronics telecommunications and information technology company 
and europes secondlargest maker of telephones thormemi of great 
britain an international seller and renter of television sets 
records and other telecommunications equipment and deutsche 
bundespost telekom the telephone company of west germany 
u s west and stc own 30 percent of the consortium thormemi 
owns 25 percent and deutsche bundespost telekom 15 percent 
u s west is the regional telephone company based in this denver 
suburb 
